HEADWORD: Apologist
<hw>A*pol"o*gist</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>apologiste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who makes an apology; one who
speaks or writes in defense of a faith, a cause, or an institution;
especially, one who argues in defense of Christianity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apologize</ent>⟦br⟧
